Ethernet only wi-fi:
   sudo systemctl start iwd.service
   iwctl
   station wlan0 scan
   station wlan0 get-networks
   station wlan0 connect TP-LINK_29D8

Find out disk space:
	df -h  

Determine the network card model:
	lspci | grep -i ethernet
	# или
	lspci | grep -i network

Copy and Cut text:
	Alt + A - selecting text.
	Ctrl + K — cuts text.
	Alt + 6 — copy don`t delete.
	Ctrl + U - insert.

Mount usb:
	fdisk -l
	sudo mkdir /mnt/usb
	sudo mount -o rw /***/*** /mnt/usb
	
Setup and Start - QTile:
	pacman -S qtile python-pywlroots xorg-xinit wayland
	qtile start
	or
	qtile start -b wayland

Place the downloaded file config.py on the way: ~/.config/qtile/config.py

Check the configuration file for syntax errors
	python -m py_compile ~/.config/qtile/config.py
	or
	qtile check

Qtile log :
	~/.local/share/qtile/qtile.log


